    "what_description": "Rosularia radicosa is a succulent plant belonging to the family Crassulaceae. It has rosettes of fleshy, glabrous leaves that are green to purple in color, often with reddish margins, and 2-5 cm in length. The leaves are oblanceolate to linear-lanceolate in shape, with a distinct midrib and crenate to dentate margins. Rosularia radicosa produces white to pinkish flowers on a branched inflorescence, with 5-6 petals that are 5-10 mm in length. This plant is native to the Himalayas and parts of China, where it grows in rocky, stony areas at high elevations.",
